===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|yielden}}, {{m|enm|yelden}}, {{m|enm|ȝelden|t=to yield, pay}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġieldan|t=to pay}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*geldan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*geldaną|t=to pay}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*gʰeldʰ-|t=to pay}}.
{{rel-top|Cognates}}
Cognate with {{cog|sco|yield||to yield}}, {{cog|frr|jilden||to pay}}, Saterland Frisian {{cog|stq|jäilde||to be valid; matter; count; be worth}}, {{cog|fy|jilde||to pay}}, Low German {{cog|nds|gellen}}, {{cog|nl|gelden||to apply, count, be valued, be regarded}}, {{cog|de|gelten||to apply, count, be valued, be regarded}}, {{cog|is|gjalda||to pay, yield, give}}, {{cog|da|gælde||to apply, count, be valued, be regarded}}, {{cog|nb|gjelde}}.
