====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[payment|Payment]]; [[tribute]].
# A [[product]]; the [[quantity]] of something produced.
#: {{ux|en|Zucchini plants always seem to produce a high '''yield''' of fruit.}}
# {{senseid|en|explosive}} The [[explosive]] [[energy]] value of a bomb, especially a [[nuke]], usually expressed in tons of [[TNT]] equivalent.
# {{lb|en|law}} The [[current]] return as a [[percentage]] of the [[price]] of a [[stock]] or [[bond]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-07-06|volume=408|issue=8843|page=68|magazine={{w|The Economist}}| title=[http://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21580518-terrible-name-interesting-trend-rise-smart-beta The rise of smart beta]| passage=Investors face a quandary. Cash offers a return of virtually zero in many developed countries; government-bond '''yields''' may have risen in recent weeks but they are still unattractive. Equities have suffered two big bear markets since 2000 and are wobbling again. It is hardly surprising that pension funds, insurers and endowments are searching for new sources of return.}}
# {{lb|en|finance}} [[profit|Profit]] earned from an [[investment]]; [[return on investment]].
